Iran and the Soviet Union haveprovisionally agreed to hold talks on a possible exchange ofIranian crude oil for finished Soviet oil products, an officialspokesman said Tuesday.    Gennady Gerasimov, chief of the Soviet Foreign Ministry'sInformation Directorate, told reporters the agreement had beenreached during a visit to Moscow last week by Iran's OilMinister Gholamreza Aqazadeh.    Gerasimov said no date had been set for the talks, whichwould also study the possibility of Soviet technical assistancefor Iran's oil industry. REUTER&#3;